**Kosovo Parliamentary Election**

The election proceeded without major disruptions, though voter turnout was lower than in previous elections. **Victoria, Australia By-Elections**

Westaway led with 51.6% of the two-party preferred vote against the Greens' Angelica Di Camillo. Independent candidate Tony Lupton's preference deal played a crucial role in the outcome. citeturn0news11

In the Werribee by-election, Labor held a narrow lead over the Liberals, with fewer than 450 votes separating them. Labor's margin in Werribee fell drastically from 10.9% to 0.6%, with their first-preference votes dropping from 45% to 28.7%. Analysts warn these results could impact Labor at the national level, especially with a federal election on the horizon. Finance Minister Katy Gallagher and Minister for Indigenous Affairs Malarndirri McCarthy acknowledged the need to address cost-of-living issues. citeturn0news13

These by-election outcomes have prompted both major parties to reassess their strategies and candidate selections to better reflect electorates' diversity and values. citeturn0news14
